<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/assets/favicon-96x96.png" sizes="96x96" />
<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/assets/favicon.svg" />
<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/assets/favicon.ico" />
<link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/assets/apple-touch-icon.png" />
<link rel="manifest" href="/assets/site.webmanifest" />
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About - What bird</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Montserrat", "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Inter", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f1f5f9 0%, #e2e8f0 100%);
            color: #334155;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            min-height: 100vh;
            line-height: 1.6;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }

        /* Main content area */
        .main-container {
            flex: 1;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 30px 7px 24px;
            width: 100%;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        .back-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            color: #64748b;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 60px;
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
            padding: 8px 0;
            align-self: flex-start;
        }

        .back-link:hover {
            color: #047857;
        }

        .content-area {
            flex: 1;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: left;
            align-items: left;
            min-height: 400px;
        }

        .content-text {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            line-height: 1.7;
            color: #475569;
            text-align: left;
            max-width: 600px;
            padding: 40px;
        }

        .placeholder-text {
            color: #000000;
            font-style: normal;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-family: Montserrat;
        }

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .main-container {
                padding: 60px 16px 16px;
            }
            
            .content-text {
                padding: 24px;
            }
            
            .placeholder-text {
                font-size: 1.1rem;
            }
        }

        /* Animation */
        @keyframes fadeInUp {
            from {
                opacity: 0;
                transform: translateY(20px);
            }
            to {
                opacity: 1;
                transform: translateY(0);
            }
        }

        .content-area {
            animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="main-container">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/>
                <path d="M19 12H5"/>
            </svg>
            Back to Home
        </a>

        <div class="content-area">
            <div class="content-text">
                <p class="placeholder-text">
                    "What Bird" is an AI-based bird identifier, offering a simple and fast tool to identify any bird species (and more). Just upload a photo, provide context, and receive an answer (not 100% accurate!). Built by Yuri Tsygankov. If you have questions, ideas, or issues, feel free to contact me via <a href="mailto:y.g.tsygankov@gmail.com">email</a> or <a href="https://x.com/lopushok09">social media</a>. Hope you love it!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
